article.headline: Houston Christian wins 86-83 against Incarnate Word
article.description: — Jay Alvarez's 25 points helped Houston Christian defeat Incarnate Word 86-83 on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Houston Christian wins 86-83 against Incarnate Word
article.story: HOUSTON -- — Jay Alvarez's 25 points helped Houston Christian defeat Incarnate Word 86-83 on Saturday night. Alvarez also contributed nine rebounds for the Huskies (6-16, 4-7 Southland Conference). Michael Imariagbe scored 18 points while going 7 of 12 and 4 of 8 from the free throw line, and added seven rebounds. Marcus Greene had 14 points and shot 5 for 10, including 3 for 5 from beyond the arc. Josiah Hammons led the way for the Cardinals (7-16, 2-8) with 22 points. Dylan Hayman added 16 points, eight rebounds and two steals for Incarnate Word. In addition, Josh Akpovwa had 14 points and three blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
